news.title: Residents of Signature View Apartments in Delhi await rent compensation from DDA
news.para: Amrendra Singh Rakesh, president of the resident welfare association (RWA) of the apartment complex, said that 111 residents have already vacated their flats though they have not yet received the promised rent compensation from the DDA.

news.title: AccuSpace buys 30,000 sq ft office space in Gurugram for Rs 62 crore
news.para: Mukesh Choudhary, Managing Director of AccuSpace, said the company has entered Delhi-NCR as part of its strategy to expand into high-growth markets.

news.title: Mortgage approvals in UK fall to six-month low in February
news.para: Lenders approved 65,481 mortgages in February, down from 66,041 in January. This was the lowest number since August and just below the median in a Reuters poll of economists which had pointed to approvals of 66,000.

news.title: Hyderabad’s real estate market faces slowdown in 2025
news.para: According to the latest reports from real estate services firms Anarock and PropEquity, residential sales in the city saw a 45% to 50% decline during this period.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body nears property tax recovery target of Rs 150 crore for FY25
news.para: Despite March 31 being a government holiday for Eid-al-Fitr, the MC has decided to keep its zonal suvidha kendras open to facilitate last-minute taxpayers.

news.title: Pune civic body offers 5-10% discount on property tax payment till June 30
news.para: Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) offers a 5% to 10% discount to taxpayers who pay their dues before May 31, every year. However, an extension of one month has been offered for financial year 2025-26.

news.title: Five ponds in Gurugram encroached upon by construction
news.para: According to MCG's response to a right to information (RTI) query filed by activist Vaishali Rana last year, ponds in Sector 50 township Nirvana Country, Badshapur, Kadarpur and Gwalpahari have been encroached on.

news.title: Odisha CM launches housing scheme for the poor in Kalahandi district
news.para: On the launch day, work orders were issued for 60,000 houses. The goal is to construct over 5 lakh houses in the next three years.

news.title: MHADA aims to construct 19,497 housing units across Maharashtra in FY26
news.para: This will be executed through its regional boards in Mumbai, Pune, Konkan, Nashik, Amravati, Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar, and Nagpur.

news.title: Over 70 RWAs slams Chandigarh administration for financially burdening residents
news.para: Chandigarh MP Manish Tewari and municipal councillor Prem Lata also attended the meeting. They lambasted the authorities for not being accountable to the public, raising serious questions over the democratic set-up of the country.

news.title: M3M India to close ₹1300 crore Indiabulls loan by Q1 FY26
news.para: The company will pay the residual amount of ₹167 crore by the first quarter of the financial year 2025-26.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat achieves 49.5 MTPA production capacity in FY25
news.para: Puneet Dalmia, managing director & CEO of the company said, "The commissioning of line-2 aligns with our long-term vision of scaling capacity to 110-130 MTPA by 2031."

news.title: NITCO assigns leasehold rights of Thane plot to Manometer India
news.para: NITCO will receive a monetary consideration of ₹11,00,000 and non-monetary consideration of 7,459.2 sq meters (80,293 sq ft) of constructed carpet area or 25% of the FSI area, whichever is higher, in the upcoming development by Manometer on the said plot.

news.title: CREDAI Bhopal mulls legal action against property rate hike
news.para: This is despite the Central Evaluation Committee (CEC), led by IG, stamps and duties, Amit Tomar, reducing the average hike in collector guideline rates for Bhopal to 11% from 14% in its meeting on Saturday.

news.title: Bidhannagar civic body extends deadline to clear property tax
news.para: The civic authorities have posted a notice on their official website, stating that property tax collection through online for all quarters of the financial year 2024-25 will stop at midnight on the coming Saturday (April 5) while payment by cash will stop after coming Friday (April 4).

news.title: DTCP seeks HC nod to conduct flat allotment draw again in Gurugram
news.para: District town and country planning department (DTCP) has filed a response in Punjab and Haryana high court seeking cancellation of the previous draw and permission for a fresh process. The next hearing is scheduled for April 1.

news.title: SC says petitioner can move HC seeking interim relief over Haryana's stilt-plus-four floor policy
news.para: The bench of justices BV Nagarathna and Prasanna B Varale were hearing a challenge to Haryana's controversial policy by Sunil Singh, a resident of Sushant Lok.

news.title: Gujarat RERA prevents bank from seizing properties of allottees
news.para: The authority emphasised that allottees have rights over the property and instructed the bank to relinquish possession of properties it already acquired pending the final order.
